					<h2>Before You Hire a Contractor or Start a Build,
Consider These Questions:</h2>				
							<ul>
							<li>
										 Are you planning for what you want, or what the market will reward?
									</li>
								<li>
										 Will your contractor respect your timeline and your budget?
									</li>
								<li>
										 Are you leveraging construction loans, renovation financing, or private capital the right way?
									</li>
								<li>
										 Will your build increase net worth, or just cost you?
									</li>
								<li>
										 Are you working with pros who understand value creation, not just craftsmanship?
									</li>
						</ul>
					<h2>Why Builders and Contractors Are Wealth Partners
</h2>				
							<ul>
							<li>
										Keep costs predictable and within lending limits
									</li>
								<li>
										Suggest build options that improve appraisal value
									</li>
								<li>
										Identify layout tweaks that reduce labor/time
									</li>
								<li>
										Get you to cash flow or resale faster
									</li>
								<li>
										Navigate permits, setbacks, and code challenges early
									</li>
						</ul>
																<a href="https://stairwaymortgage.com/schedule-call/">
							<img width="1024" height="683" src="/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/emma-houghton-EixJzIdl4bc-unsplash-1024x683.jpg" alt="" srcset="/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/emma-houghton-EixJzIdl4bc-unsplash-1024x683.jpg 1024w, /wp-content/uploads/2025/06/emma-houghton-EixJzIdl4bc-unsplash-300x200.jpg 300w, /wp-content/uploads/2025/06/emma-houghton-EixJzIdl4bc-unsplash-768x512.jpg 768w, /wp-content/uploads/2025/06/emma-houghton-EixJzIdl4bc-unsplash-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, /wp-content/uploads/2025/06/emma-houghton-EixJzIdl4bc-unsplash-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, /wp-content/uploads/2025/06/emma-houghton-EixJzIdl4bc-unsplash-1065x710.jpg 1065w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" />								</a>
<strong>Real Project Spotlight</strong><br><br>
A first-time investor bought a 1950s duplex with a 2-month flip plan. The contractor in our network proposed a layout change that cost \$6K more upfront—but reduced construction time by 3 weeks and pushed the resale \$35K higher thanks to added living space.<br><br>
Speed + Smarts = Profit
					<h2>When to Bring in a Builder or Contractor
</h2>				
							<ul>
							<li>
										You’re flipping or renting a fixer
									</li>
								<li>
										You’re adding a garage, ADU, or in-law suite
									</li>
								<li>
										You’re buying new construction or building custom
									</li>
								<li>
										You’re buying distressed property below market value
									</li>
								<li>
										You’re doing cash-out refi and need renovation bids
									</li>
						</ul>
